pr_body:
Multiple fixes and enhancements to Ethernet and LLC decoders. Summary of changes:
+ VLAN tags are organized into 2 new classes: VLANtag8021Q and VLANtagISL, contained in a new list field "Ethernet.vlan_tags";
+ MPLS labels are similarly a new class MPLSlabel, contained in a new list field "Ethernet.mpls_labels";
+ support IEEE 802.1Q double tagging (aka QinQ);
+ Ethernet/IEEE 802.3 Ethernet can be constructed with MPLS labels and/or VLAN tags;
+ fixed construction of LLC with SAP/SNAP headers and data encapsulation;
+ fixed parsing of Cisco ISL VLAN tag (was off by 1 bit);
+ correctly compute len() of Ethernet with tags/labels and LLC;
+ compute 802.3 Ethernet Frame Check Sequence (FCS), recognize trailer bytes;
+ added a bunch of unit tests.

Changes are backward compatible, except the following:
+ LLC is now a layer. This matches Wireshark representation, and I believe it was meant to be this way originally in dpkt, but eventually llc.py unpacking code was moved into ethernet.py. I guess it was moved to deal with circular referencing between the two modules. I found a solution that avoids these issues.
+ As a result of the above change, LLC.data that is now properly decoded to the next layer (previously one had to explicitly cast it, e.g. ip.IP(llc.data)).

Fixes #59, #83, #89, #140, #148

I've refactored the code so that `hashin` can be used as a library (#29).

```python
import hashin
hashin.get_package_hashes('hashin')
```

